## üöÄ Phase 2: Transaction DocTypes (NEXT)

### Priority 1: Item Receipt
**Purpose:** Receive items from Purchase Department into store

**DocType:** Store Item Receipt
- **Fields:**
  - Receipt number (auto-generated)
  - Receipt date
  - Purchase Order reference (optional)
  - Supplier reference
  - Items table (item, quantity, UOM, batch/serial, location)
  - Received by
  - Status (Draft, Submitted, Cancelled)

- **Features:**
  - Auto-create serial numbers if enabled
  - Batch number entry with expiry date
  - Multi-item receipt
  - Print receipt voucher
  - Update stock on submit

### Priority 2: Item Issue
**Purpose:** Issue items to factory operations/departments

**DocType:** Store Item Issue
- **Fields:**
  - Issue number (auto-generated)
  - Issue date
  - Work Order reference (optional)
  - Department/Cost Center
  - Requested by
  - Items table (item, requested qty, issued qty, UOM, batch/serial, from location)
  - Issued by
  - Status (Draft, Submitted, Returned, Cancelled)

- **Features:**
  - Check stock availability
  - Serial/batch selection
  - Partial issue support
  - Print issue voucher
  - Return functionality
  - Update stock on submit

### Priority 3: Item Requisition
**Purpose:** Request items before issuing (approval workflow)

**DocType:** Store Item Requisition
- **Fields:**
  - Requisition number (auto-generated)
  - Requisition date
  - Required date
  - Department/Cost Center
  - Requested by
  - Items table (item, quantity, UOM, purpose)
  - Approved by
  - Status (Draft, Pending, Approved, Rejected, Issued)

- **Features:**
  - Multi-level approval workflow
  - Create Issue from Requisition
  - Email notifications
  - Print requisition form

